		<td><b>NES Modifications</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The easiest mod, involves removing the metal bar, so you can put carts with EPROMs in, else they won't fit.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMods_Remove_Metal_Piece.jpg">http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMod ... _Piece.jpg</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Next, to disable the chip that give you that annoying flashing screen,
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMods_Disable_Lockout_Chip.jpg">http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMod ... t_Chip.jpg</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />And finally, this mod (a 100K resistor in series with a 4.7uF non-polarized cap) gives you sound input on pin 18 (EXP). If you combine it with a modified Famicom-&gt;NES converter, you can get sound from Famicom games that have a sound chip. Just solder a wire from the Famicom side pin 46 (sound out) to NES pin 18.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMods_Sound_Input_On_Pin_18.jpg">http://www.54.org/condev/NESMods/NESMod ... Pin_18.jpg</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


