	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm in an electronics class, and when you leave something floating, it tends to pick up charges that are in the air...
<br />
<br />For example, I had a binary -&gt; decimal 7-segment encoder, and I left the inputs of that floating, and the display kept showing really weird stuff, like "in between 6-7", it'd drift to 9, it'd go to 3, it'd do really weirdo floaty stuff.
<br />
<br />Not necesarilly bad, but if you want the input to be a definitive 0, without a doubt a 0, then put it to gnd.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


