	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>drk421</b> [ Mon Mar 21, 2005 6:46 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">system or to the Famicom-to-NES converter<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Both.
<br />
<br />For the Famicom-&gt;NES adapter...
<br />Just solder pin 18 on the NES side of the connector to pin 46 of the Famicom side of the connector.
<br />
<br />For the NES,
<br />Solder pin 18 of the NES cart connector to a series resistor 100K then a 1uF or higher non-polarized cap to pin 3 of the EXP connector on the bottom.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


